headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had 19 points, 19 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Washington Wizards completed a 106-92 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night after All-Star guard Bradley Beal's injury-shortened outing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook, Wizards beat Pistons 106-92 despite Beal injury

events.name: New York Knicks at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Alec Burks and RJ Barrett each scored 21 points to help the New York Knicks to a 102-96 victory Saturday night over the Milwaukee Bucks, who were without Giannis Antetokounmpo and three other injured starters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burks, Barrett help Knicks stave off short-handed Bucks

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. scored 25 points in his return to Houston’s lineup, John Wall had 13 points and 12 assists and the Rockets rebounded to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 129-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter scores 25 points, Rockets beat Timbewolves 129-107

events.name: Chicago Bulls at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl scored 20 points, DeMar DeRozan had 17 and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat Chicago 120-104 on Saturday night in Nikola Vucevic’s debut with the Bulls, snapping a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl, DeRozan lead Spurs past Bulls in Vucevic's debut

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 38 points, including 10 during New Orleans' 18-8 run in the final 3:42, and Nickiel Alexander-Walker added 20 to lift the Pelicans to a 112-103 victory over the short-handed Dallas Mavericks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson scores 38, Pelicans use late run to top Mavericks

events.name: Boston Celtics at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 20 of his 27 points in the second half and the Boston Celtics rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 111-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 27 points, Celtics rally to beat Thunder 111-94

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 35 points and seven assists to lead the Utah Jazz to a 126-110 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 35, leads Jazz past Grizzlies 126-110

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 28 points, Terance Mann added a season-high 23 and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated the Philadelphia 76ers 122-112 on Saturday night in their first game against former coach Doc Rivers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard leads Clippers past 76ers in Rivers' first game back

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer after catching an inbounds pass from the opposite end of the court and the Sacramento Kings beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 100-98 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings beat Cavs on Barnes' 3-pointer at the buzzer
